        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 22 at 5:10AM EDT until June 22 at 6:15AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>SVRBGM

The National Weather Service in Binghamton has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southern Otsego County in central New York...
Delaware County in central New York...
Eastern Cortland County in central New York...
Chenango County in central New York...

* Until 615 AM EDT.

* At 509 AM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Truxton to near Pitcher to near Guilford to
near Davenport, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Oneonta, Norwich, Sidney, Walton, Delhi, Davenport, Guilford,
Roxbury, Colchester, and Maryland.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Heavy rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to flash
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
